column3: Automatic sanity-testing: PASSED, see http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-tester/p4731_c53b1ece1b0644bd9620773eea3757bf939a678f/ for binaries and test log.\nThis test script verifies pulls every time they are updated. It, however, dies sometimes and fails to test properly.  If you are waiting on a test, please check timestamps to verify that the test.log is moving at http://jenkins.bluematt.me/pull-te
Heh, I can't even find a `-q` in the documentation for `git log`.\n

Looks like for git -q in general means 'quiet mode' mode, but I cannot find it documented for `git log` anywhere either.\nAnyhow - I'm going to use the new version of the script to merge this, and if that works, ACK.\n
